cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with semantic image retrieval problems in computer vision using deep supervised hashing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep learning-based model, which involves the use of a loss function and optimization strategy, indicating that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The experiments involve large-scale benchmark databases, which could also place it under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of semantic labels, indicating that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
